SIMPLE: listen
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Listen
<hw>Lis"ten</hw> <pr>(l⟦icr⟧s"'n)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Listened</conjf>
<pr>(l⟦icr⟧s"'nd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Listening</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[OE. <ets>listnen</ets>,
<ets>listen</ets>, <ets>lustnen</ets>, <ets>lusten</ets>, AS.
<ets>hlystan</ets>; akin to <ets>hlyst</ets> hearing, OS.
<ets>hlust</ets>, Icel. <ets>hlusta</ets> to listen, <ets>hlust</ets>
ear, AS. <ets>hlosnian</ets> to wait in suspense, OHG.
<ets>hlos⟦emac⟧n</ets> to listen, Gr. <grk>kly`ein</grk>, and E.
<ets>loud</ets>. ⟦root⟧41. See <er>Loud</er>, and cf. <er>List</er> to
listen.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To give close attention with the purpose
of hearing; to give ear; to hearken; to attend.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When we have occasion to <qex>listen</qex>, and give a more
particular attention to some sound, the tympanum is drawn to a more than
ordinary tension.</q> <rj><qau>Holder.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To give heed; to yield to advice; to follow
admonition; to obey.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Listen</qex> to me, and by me be ruled.</q>
<rj><qau>Tennyson.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>To listen after</b></col>, <cd>to take an interest
in.</cd> <mark>[Obs.]</mark></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Soldiers note forts, armories, and magazines; scholars <qex>listen
after</qex> libraries, disputations, and professors.</q>
<rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj></p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- To attend; hearken. See
<er>Attend</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Listen</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Listen
<hw>Lis"ten</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To attend to.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Listener</ent>⟦br⟧
